title: For Sale:  KIMBER ELITE CARRY 1 OF 1200 MADE
location: Upper Saddle River, New Jersey, United States
postcontent: This is a very rare 1911 pistol hand fitted and made by KIMBER back in 1998. The pistol is in practicality MINT condition. It has only been test fired a few times. Round count is far under 50. This example comes from Kimber's Custom Shop (at the time) and is called the "ELITE CARRY".ONLY 1200 OF THESE WERE EVER PRODUCED!!It has a 4" barrel and checkered rosewood grips. By far the sweetest shooting Kimber I ever had the pleasure of using, it shoots just as smoothly as my Wilson Combat CQB does. My research tells me this is all hand fitted and on a series 70 platform with no Schwartz safety and is considered a series 1 example. I contacted Kimber and they told me these are very highly desired pistols because of all the manual attention put into it. It has night sights, 20lpi front checkering, and an ambidextrous safety. It also has some special kind of melted treatment done to it. Please look up the pistol on the Internet for all specifications. I purchased this as an investment as I was told it would go up in value. Some Kimber fans told me I could get about $1500 for this pistol in such pristine condition. I'm asking the same amount I put into it, $1150 + shipping (OBO). I do not have a local FFL that does transfers. Please make sure your FFL will take firearms from non FFL holders. Shipping with insurance to your FFL is about $85 via UPS. I will take a bank check but if you want to use PayPal, you must pay using the "friends & family" feature. If you would rather use the "goods and services" option, kindly add 4% to the total amount (shipping fee included). I will ship the same day as I have both a copy of your FFL and cleared funds. Please contact me if you have any questions or concerns. Thanks for looking!!
